And he was in a coma for six years.

49:39.276 --> 49:44.682
And his wife went to his bedside and talked to him about ordinary life.

49:45.100 --> 49:47.322
And he recovered, and he's fine.

49:47.382 --> 49:49.004
And you read this after you wrote the book.

49:49.505 --> 49:52.648
I read those two things when I had started writing it.

49:52.688 --> 49:54.890
I guess I was about 50 or 60 pages into it.

49:55.311 --> 49:58.954
And so I looked upon that as a nod from the universe.

49:59.155 --> 50:03.479
And then I called Mary Kay Blakely and said, Hey, Mary Kay, Mary Kay, you were in a coma.

50:03.519 --> 50:07.283
You want to read this manuscript and see if it sounds right?

50:07.743 --> 50:08.304
And she did.

50:08.544 --> 50:09.285
And she said, yeah.

50:09.502 --> 50:11.365
Well, that was enough research.

50:11.505 --> 50:15.190
But where did you get the idea for that particular... Between 20 minutes up and up, huh?

50:15.210 --> 50:18.615
We have a sleeping cat over there in a basket in the kitchen, too.

50:18.675 --> 50:19.716
A shadow.

50:20.017 --> 50:20.738
A shadow.

50:20.758 --> 50:21.879
He's as old as Jenny.

50:23.121 --> 50:29.450
So you have a number of animals around, which is... We used to have two dogs and two cats.

50:31.492 --> 50:32.674
The idea for the premise...

50:32.958 --> 50:37.204
of this freak accident which sends Jay off into this coma.

50:37.224 --> 50:39.207
I had a girlfriend that that happened to.

50:39.227 --> 50:43.493
She didn't go in a coma, but she was walking by a building and the ice went... Jeez.

50:43.953 --> 50:45.015
So it really hurt her.

50:45.175 --> 50:48.400
It really hurt her neck.

50:48.540 --> 50:51.964
But she didn't get knocked out or anything.

50:51.985 --> 50:55.229
No, it's sort of silly, isn't it?

50:55.249 --> 50:56.671
But it just goes to show you.

50:56.731 --> 51:00.136
I mean, the most amazing things happen that way.

51:00.156 --> 51:00.957
You know, you...

51:01.831 --> 51:02.852
That's how life is.

51:02.872 --> 51:04.454
It's so sloppy and common.

51:04.494 --> 51:08.819
But the idea of putting him into a coma as the means to go through all of this.

51:09.059 --> 51:11.042
And how long is the coma in the novel, by the way?

51:11.082 --> 51:12.443
I don't think I was alert to that.

51:13.905 --> 51:16.768
I think it's three or four months.

51:16.788 --> 51:18.390
And is that common, uncommon?

51:18.410 --> 51:19.131
Does this happen?

51:19.832 --> 51:21.233
It really, really varies.

51:21.634 --> 51:22.435
This is mine here?

51:22.475 --> 51:22.715
Yeah.

51:22.995 --> 51:23.536
Oh, boy.

51:23.976 --> 51:25.638
Wait, should I put it on a plate?

51:25.658 --> 51:26.479
No, it's fine.

51:27.340 --> 51:28.041
Like some milk?

51:28.321 --> 51:28.902
No, thanks.

51:29.911 --> 51:30.552
You don't?

51:30.732 --> 51:31.774
And I'm not a milkman.

51:31.794 --> 51:34.677
Oh, well, you better have something to drink with it, though.

51:34.697 --> 51:35.418
What will it be?

51:35.458 --> 51:35.899
I have water.

51:35.919 --> 51:36.520
It would be nice.

51:37.742 --> 51:38.442
You want a martini?

51:40.485 --> 51:42.528
I love martini.

51:42.548 --> 51:42.909
And here?

51:43.790 --> 51:44.711
The only one.

51:44.851 --> 51:47.395
That's like a Bombay Sapphire.

51:47.735 --> 51:48.256
It has to be.

51:49.738 --> 51:53.403
That's the indulgence at our home on Saturday nights.

51:53.443 --> 51:59.511
My wife has a gin and tonic, and I do have an extra dry, like I walk by with a removed martini.

51:59.531 --> 51:59.631
Okay.

52:00.877 --> 52:02.080
Here's how you do the remove.

52:02.862 --> 52:06.051
You hold the glass up and say, and that's it.

52:06.733 --> 52:12.247
And, if you really want the martini, you can use these.

52:12.267 --> 52:13.831
Which idea?

52:13.932 --> 52:14.814
Onion stuffed dollars.

52:15.897 --> 52:16.759
Just spray it.

